A worrying aspect of the virus lockdown is that the ANC could use its virtually unfettered emergency powers to push through the radical social engineering it has failed to achieve in a parliamentary democracy. There seems to be a strong puritanical element within the organisation which seeks to remove health “evils” from society permanently … hence the sweeping powers to restrict the sale of alcohol and cigarettes. Disaster powers have also been used to fast-track water supplies, while talk of “mobilising” private health sector resources for the national Covid-19 fight is also accelerating the move towards the planned National Health...